						<div class="postbody">Cool! The simulator does exactly what I was asking for.<br /><br />I tried tepples' code, changing the terminator in my string to $FF, but I would keep getting 256 of that wrong tile. I then changed the routine into<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">@printstring:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda mystring,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bmi @printdone<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #$0E<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2007<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;inx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bne @printstring</div><br />which would print 256 of the tile $0E as expected. It seems I'm still not reading values from mystring into A properly, or I would only have printed out 5 of $0E before branching into @printdone.</div>

